Can you be more specific about how would you like to use ONNX Runtime inferencing on Android devices?
- Are you developing an App or a shared library? What do you want to achieve on mobile devices using ONNX Runtime?
- Are there any specific reasons that you cannot use Android Studio?
- What is your current setup for developing on Android?
- Do you have requirements for cross-platform development? e.g., developing Apps can run on both iOS and Android, or share the code between desktop and mobile
- What is your preferred API? Such as C/C++, java/kotlin, js(React Native), c#(Xamarin)

Thanks for reaching out. 
I want to use the C++ API.
I am using a Linux system and have under development prototype device to test inferencing. 
I am developing a shared library. I want to use it for inferencing of Computer Vision IPs. 
Yes there are reasons to not use Android studio. 

Just to update regarding the progress. I was able to build the onnxruntime library for Linux, but upon trying to build for Android, I am running into issues.
Steps I followed:
1) Clone the onnxruntime repo
2) Made changes to the CMakeLists to enable NNAPI support
3) Built it using the command: `./build.sh --android --android_sdk_path ~/android/android-sdk-linux --android_ndk_path ~/android/android-ndk-r19c --android_abi arm64-v8a --android_api 28`
But I am stuck with the error:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30999857/151959787-42c028e0-91fc-4874-8479-33508aded16c.png)
The required .so files couldn't be generated. Any guidance on rectifying the issue would be appreciated.
Or if any other alternative ways to approach the overall task, do let me know.

Like the Linux version, just in case if your team has any precompiled .so files for Android with Android ABI: arm64-v8a and Android API: 28 do let me know.

You don't need to modify the CMakeList to enable NNAPI support, you may add `--use_nnapi` to your build command.
Try to use NDK 21+, we use NDK 21/23 in our building system.

There is another way to obtain the ONNX Runtime mobile shared C/C++ library and headers without building it, see, https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/install/#cc-1
Please note the packages in the about link on Maven Central are the reduced-sized ORT version for mobile, if you want to try the full ORT for Android, you may want to try the packages available [here](https://github.com/gwang-msft/unofficial_onnxruntime_mobile_releases)

Hi Team,
I was trying to build it again this time with NDK  21 as suggested, however it seems to fail in a similar way again. Kindly guide me on how to troubleshoot and fix the problem.
Command used: `./build.sh --android --android_sdk_path ~/android/android-sdk-linux --android_ndk_path ~/android/android-ndk-r21e/android-ndk-r21e --android_abi arm64-v8a --android_api 28`

```
[ 97%] Linking CXX executable onnxruntime_test_all
clang++: error: unable to execute command: Killed
clang++: error: linker command failed due to signal (use -v to see invocation)
```

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30999857/152319668-fb6bd4e7-335d-4f6a-9d9b-791f05a7aa36.png)

Regarding the reduced size package available on MavenCentral which version of Android ABI and Android API was used for generating it? Could you let me know from where/ how to download the aar file from mavencentral?
Is the aar file available for download at [https://javalibs.com/artifact/com.microsoft.onnxruntime/onnxruntime-mobile] -an official one?

We have never seen this error before, and information included is too generic to diagnostic the issue.
Please add this to `cmake/CMakeLists.txt` 
```
add_link_options(-v)
```
And paste the detailed error message here. (or the entire build log, upload to some shared space if the log is too long)

The official AAR package available on Maven Central is built for all Android ABIs, and using API level 21, it can be downloaded here https://search.maven.org/artifact/com.microsoft.onnxruntime/onnxruntime-mobile/1.10.0/aar

Thanks for the valuable information. If I can build it without errors I would prefer that over using prebuilt packages.

I have made the changes as requested in the CMakeLists and have uploaded the build log here:
[onnxruntime_ndk21_build_log.txt](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/8000901/onnxruntime_ndk21_build_log.txt)

Would be grateful if you could review the log and get back on any possible fix I could utilize. Thanks
